TITLE: X's Tumultuous First Year Under Elon Musk, in Charts
SUMMARY: The platform is struggling to attract users and advertisers, third-party data suggest. Musk has voiced optimism, saying the company “can be thought of as an inverse startup.”

TITLE: Exxon, Chevron Invest in the West as Global Conflicts Increase
SUMMARY: The two largest Western crude producers are focusing their investments closer to home as the world gets more dangerous.

TITLE: Toyota Chairman Says People Are Finally Seeing Reality on EVs
SUMMARY: Akio Toyoda said the electric-vehicle industry was coming to recognize that there isn’t a single answer to reducing carbon emissions.

TITLE: Boeing Cuts 737 Delivery Goal for Year
SUMMARY: Boeing posted a $1.64 billion loss for the quarter ended Sept. 30 and reported negative cash flow from its operations.

TITLE: Apple Risks Getting Caught in Taiwan Tensions With iPhone Supplier Probes
SUMMARY: China’s investigations into Taiwanese supplier Foxconn come as its billionaire founder pursues a bid for the Taiwanese presidency.

TITLE: GM Scales Back EV Plans as Buyers Hesitate
SUMMARY: The automaker is abandoning a self-imposed target to build 400,000 electric vehicles by mid-2024.

TITLE: Chevron to Buy Hess for $53 Billion
SUMMARY: The all-stock deal is the latest sign of consolidation in an oil-and-gas industry flush with cash.

TITLE: Electric Cars Were Already Having Issues. Then Things Got Political.
SUMMARY: The 2024 race for the White House is reigniting the debate over EVs.

TITLE: Inside Meta, Debate Over What's Fair in Suppressing Comments in the Palestinian Territories
SUMMARY: The Instagram and Facebook owner has been wrestling with how to best enforce its content rules in the midst of a brutal and chaotic war.

TITLE: Hollywood Actors, Studios to Restart Contract Negotiations
SUMMARY: Talks are scheduled to resume Tuesday after some high-profile SAG-Aftra members offer additional dues and press for progress.
